<TITLE> Tongi fire guts 100 shanties, warehouses </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, Feb 27 (bdnews24.com)A fire burnt about 50 warehouses of fabric off-cuts and as many shanties near People's Ceramic Factory in Tongi, locals said. As the blaze spread, local people started running for safety. No-one was injured though. The fire gutted at least 50 houses in the neighbouring Namapara slum. The locals said about 50 small warehouses built for storing fabric off-cuts from garment factories had also been gutted. Around 1pm, one such warehouse caught fire, which spread fast to other warehouses. The blaze also spread to the Namapara slum, witnesses said. Tongi fire station officer Hiran Miah told reporters that nobody was injured. Fire fighters controlled the blaze before it could spread to People's Ceramic Factory. bdnews24.com/
